"id":304,
"zh":"大家都同意「寧可冒著失去朋友的危險,也不能少了笑料」是件傻事。但是很少人想過失去朋友有多麼容易:朋友間的醜角靠著朋友對自己的重視,才敢對朋友比對其他人放肆,而且少考慮到我們所愛的人對我們的傷害會有多深。再怎麼緊密的交情,也沒辦法保障這樣的自由;而且仗著是朋友就能這麼做,實在是矛盾不通;除非我們能說,朋友對我們造成的傷害比其他人所造成的更小。",
"en":"It is generally agreed to be Folly, to hazard the Loss of a Friend, rather than lose a Jest. But few consider how easily a Friend may be thus lost, Depending on the known Regard their Friends have for them. Jesters take more Freedom with Friends than they would dare to do with others, little thinking how much deeper we are wounded by an Affront from one we love. But the strictest Intimacy can never warrant Freedoms of this Sort; and it is indeed preposterous to think they should; unless we can suppose Injuries are less Evils when they are done us by Friends, than when they come from other Hands.",
